    • Constructor Detail

      • DataType

        public DataType(java.lang.String name,
                double min,
                double max,
                java.lang.String type,
                java.lang.String[] aliases)
         throws java.lang.Exception
        Constructor. Note that the type should be taken from one of the public static variables in this class.
        Parameters:
        min - the minimum value for this data type
        max - the maximum value for this data type
        precision - the precision for this data type
        type - the type of number represented by this data type. This value should be taken from the public static variables defined in this class.
        aliases - one or more names given to this type.
        name - the proper monarch name of the DataType. This should equate to one of (INT, LONG, FLOAT, DOUBLE, STRING) from the above static definitions.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception
